Parliament, Tuesday, 06 March 2018 – The Portfolio Committee on Justice and Correctional Services and the Portfolio Committee on Police will tomorrow have a joint meeting to receive a briefing from the National Prosecuting Authority (NPA) on progress and challenges in the prosecution of state capture cases. The meeting will also be attended by the Directorate of Priority Crime Investigation. Details of the meeting are as follows: 
	
	Date: 07 March 2018
	Time: 9:00 am
	Venue: Committee Room V475, Fourth Floor, Old Assembly Building ISSUED BY PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE PORTFOLIO COMMITTEE ON JUSTICE AND CORRECTIONAL SERVICES, DR MATHOLE MOTSHEKGA For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairperson, please contact the committee’s Media Officer: Name: Rajaa Azzakani (Ms)
	Tel: 021 403 8437
	Cell: 081 703 9542
	E-mail: razzakani@parliament.gov.za The room in which a House meets to debate is called a “Chamber”.Read more